Rhinoplasty or nose job, is a cosmetic surgery procedure that changes the anatomy of a person’s nose. Rhinoplasty can remove a bump, narrow the nose, straighten the nose, make the tip more refined, and elevate the tip.

My philosophy on rhinoplasty is that patients should always look like themselves – that changes should be natural and refined. In the long run, conservative surgery preserves results longer and minimizes scar tissue formation that can distort the nose resulting in an “overdone” look.

#rhinoplasty #plasticsurgery

node.text:
I want you all to meet Tyler who was born with 2 extra nipples.  I performed a surgical removal of the extra nipples on my TV show Dr. 90210.  I truly enjoyed getting to know Tyler who is a pre-med student and had a true interest in surgery and science and I am so excited for her future. 

Extra nipples or supernumerary nipples occur in 1-6% of the population and many people don’t even realize they have them since they usually get mistaken for a mole or birthmark in the armpit or on the chest or abdomen.  The extra nipples sit along the milk line - as they do with other mammals.

The extra nipples range in size from being very small to actually having breast tissue under them and in the majority of cases they are benign but it still important to get them checked out by a doctor like any other pigmented lesion. Many patients like Tyler do choose to have them removed for comfort reasons because sometimes they catch or rub on clothing.  They can easily be excised under local anesthesia and usually only a a few sutures are needed. #plasticsurgery #dr90210 @surgeon

Dr. Cat Begovic is a board-certified plastic surgeon in Los Angeles and Beverly Hills, California. She graduated from Harvard University with Honors in Molecular and Cellular biology. From there she was awarded her medical degree at UCLA, where she also finished two surgical residencies. Dr. Cat has been in private practice since June 2010. Dr. Cat is also a cast member of the TV Show Dr. 90210 on E! and the founder of the luxury skincare brand MD GLAM.
Dr. Cat specializes in tummy tuck, labiaplasty, mommy makeover, liposuction, breast augmentation, BBL, revision plastic surgery, and other highly skilled plastic surgery procedures.

I wanted to share with you this stunning transformation of my patient @brookebarrows whose inspiring story was shared on Dr. 90210. Brooke lost over 200 pounds through diet and exercise - her tummy tuck to remove the excess remaining skin and tighten her abdominal wall was the finishing touch after all that hard work.  Her results are so natural, you can’t even tell she had surgery done. She is a successful plus sized model and models a lot of swimwear and two-piece outfits. When I performed this surgery - I took into consideration all the little details - keeping her scar thin and low and symmetric, creating my “signature natural looking belly button”, shaping her waist and abdomen to create the appearance of abs, and all the while keeping her curves.  Brooke - I feel so blessed to have you as my patient, thank you for being so inspiring, and I am so excited for all the amazing things your future holds. @surgeon

#dr90210 #plasticsurgeon #tummytuck

I specialize in labiaplasty and vaginal rejuvenation.  For those of you who aren’t familiar with these terms, labiaplasty is a plastic surgery procedure that reduces and reshapes the labia minora.  Over 10 years ago I authored a book chapter on this topic, and then since then from doing hundreds of labiaplasties and studying the anatomy and aesthetics of this area, I have developed my very own surgical technique that creates a natural looking, tucked in, symmetric shape, little to no pain and an almost invisible scar. I often combine this with clitoral hood reduction in order to create an even and gentle curve that blends seamlessly.  

However what makes me a pioneer in vaginal cosmetic surgery is not just my surgical techniques, but more so that I have helped bring the topic of vaginal cosmetic surgery to the forefront of every day conversation.  Through my social media, you tube videos, and TV shows and media interviews on this topic, I have helped to make talking about vaginal cosmetic surgery not taboo.  Through educating the public on why women seek this surgery and creating a better understanding of what women can do to seek solutions for this area of the body, it has helped break the barrier of embarrassment related to this topic. Women who seek labiaplasty complain of discomfort because of rubbing or twisting of the labia, issues with hygiene, avoidance of leggings, swimwear or other tight fitting clothing, or because they feel self conscious during intimacy because of labial asymmetry or excess labial show and volume. It significantly improves the quality of life for women who seek this surgery. Im so proud of Jessi and I admire her courage for sharing her labiaplasty journey on Dr. 90210 #labiaplasty #thepussycatdolls

What is the difference between skin and fat?

My patient from Episode 3 of my show Dr. 90210 wanted to get her pre baby body back after pregnancy and thought she had a lot of abdominal fat after pregnancy but in fact it was mostly excess skin.

A tummy tuck repairs the abdominal muscles, tightens the abdominal wall and removes and tightens excess skin.  Liposuction removes and thins excess fat.

Ashley first had a tummy tuck and then liposuction of her back and waist with fat transfer to her butt.  She did not have liposuction to her abdomen.
You can see how the tummy tuck alone created a flat and contoured natural looking abdomen and using my special belly button technique she has a natural looking “innie” belly button with hidden scar.  Her tummy tuck incision is low and thin.  The liposuction with fat transfer accentuated the waist.  She has a beautiful result and I am so grateful to be her surgeon #dr90210 @surgeon #plasticsurgery #tummytuck

node.text:
“Dr. Cat Begovic says her plastic surgery practice is “at least five times busier” than before “Dr. 90210” premiered amid the coronavirus pandemic.

The 43-year-old said her “mommy makeovers” — which include the midsection, body contouring, breast surgery and even vaginal cosmetic surgery — are in high demand.

“I think it’s more just because people are at home, they’re able to work from home, able to care for themselves a little better,” she told Page Six. “They had their caretaker with them usually, whereas normally they would have to block off a huge amount of time, make more arrangements in order to be able to recover from surgery. So I think that people being able to relax and rest and give themselves the time and care they need after surgery has made it definitely busier for plastic surgery in general.”

node.text:
This came up just now as a memory on my FB page.  It was August 30, 2012 and I had just delivered my daughter Layla via C-section. I had only taken 2 weeks off and I was back at work operating and apparently back in the gym.

I cannot believe that I did that and even worse that I took pride in doing that.  Being a woman in a man’s field and having fought so hard to prove myself, somehow I had been indoctrinated into thinking that taking time off to have a child, or resting was a sign of weakness.  I remember in my surgical residency my colleagues rolling their eyes or making rude comments whenever one of us female surgeons had our period and had to step out, or if someone had to leave a little early (likely at 8 pm, not even early mind you) to care for a child.  So over the years, the system made me think these things were negatives.  For most of my life I was just constantly pushing myself to succeed, to sacrifice myself and important things like health, family, and self care, because I believed that it was necessary to do so to succeed or compete in a man’s world.  But there is no such competition.  Being a mom, a person recovering from surgery, and just being a woman was enough. And success is defined by so so many things - who you are as a whole person, not just one part of it.

Seeing this post makes me sad and mad at the same time.  That 9 years ago, I did not have the awareness to choose the correct priorities.  That I was blinded by the idea that I needed to “do it all” or be a woman competing in a man’s world.  Women have their own amazing incomparable world, and as  women we can live, thrive, and shine even more brightly in our own lane.  A woman’s power comes from things that are uniquely feminine - there is no competition with men - the only competition is with our ideas in our minds.  If there were anything I could tell my younger self in medical school, residency, and early in my career - it would be that.  Family, love, health, well-being, self-care, self-compassion.  So grateful for all the blessing in my life and for being a woman in her own world ❤️ #divinefeminine

Rhinoplasty or nose job, is a cosmetic surgery procedure that changes the anatomy of a person’s nose. Rhinoplasty can remove a bump, narrow the nose, straighten the nose, make the tip more refined, and elevate the tip.

My philosophy on rhinoplasty is that patients should always look like themselves – that changes should be natural and refined. In the long run, conservative surgery preserves results longer and minimizes scar tissue formation that can distort the nose resulting in an “overdone” look.

#rhinoplasty #plasticsurgery

Taking care of your skin is even more important if you are active and have a busy lifestyle such as school, career, or being a mom.  The stress, sweat and dirt can build up on your skin, clog pores, cause breakouts and the harsh exposures to sun, wind, and environmental toxins can damage and age your skin.  Using the MD GLAM DAY moisturizer and SUNSHOUT SPF50 before you start your day, both of which are rich in anti-oxidants and also hydrating agents helps protect your skin during the day.  Both also feel and smell light and absorb quickly so your skin won’t feel greasy.  

Cleansing your skin after a long work or school day, or any day is really important! You want to remove the dirt and sweat that has collected, cleanse your pores, but at the same time, not over-strip your skin of protective oils. I truly look forward at the end of every day to using the MD GLAM DEEP PORE CLEANSER and truly love using the very yummy EXFOLIATING ENZYME SCRUB for extra exfoliation. It’s literally my aahhh moment having my skin feel so fresh and clean.

Finally, nothing beats the feeling of using the RETINOL-C EYE SERUM followed by the HYALURONIC C-COMPLEX NIGHT moisturizer.  I can feel my skin soaking up all the hydrating and collagen building ingredients and know that in the morning my skin will feel so soft and supple.
@mymdglam products are paraben-free, sulfate-free, dye-free, petroleum-free, with NO ANIMAL TESTING.  MD GLAM is cruelty free certified by Leaping Bunny and is manufactured in the USA. 💕💕

node.text:
CoolSculpting vs Plastic Surgery? 

Many of you have asked me about my opinion on CoolSculpting. I personally do not believe it is a good treatment and I would never do it on myself so therefore I would never do it on a patient.

CoolSculpting creates significant scar of the tissues.  For any of you who have watched my surgeries where I have had to do revisions on CoolSculpting, you have seen the hard scar tissue it creates under the skin through all the fat.  It does NOT remove fat the way liposuction does or tighten skin the way tummy tuck does.  Also in some cases it actually causes the fat to grow - something called paradoxical adipose hyperplasia.  I advise patients to get a consultation first so I can evaluate their anatomy and discuss surgical and non surgical options.  That way they can make the best possible informed  decision for themselves.

If you are interested in scheduling a consultation with me please visit beautybydrcat.com and submit the consultation form on the website or call my office at 310-858-8808. 
#coolsculpting #liposuction #tummytuck
